        <mi>c</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle c}</annotatio=
n>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/86a67b81c2de995bd608d5b2df50cd8cd7d92455" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.338ex; width:1.007ex; height:1.676ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle c}"=
></span> in the figure). The sides adjacent to the right angle are called <=
i>legs</i> (or <i>catheti</i>, singular: <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
