{2}+b^{2}=3Dc^{2}.}"></span> If the lengths of all three sides of a right t=
riangle are integers, the triangle is called a <b>Pythagorean triangle</b> =
and its side lengths are collectively known as a <i><a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Pythagorean_triple" title=3D"Pythagorean triple">Pythagor=
ean triple</a></i>.
</p><p>The relations between the sides and angles of a right triangle provi=
des one way of defining and understanding <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Trigonometry" title=3D"Trigonometry">trigonometry</a>, the study of=
 the metrical relationships between lengths and angles.
</p>
