-align: -1.838ex; width:24.238ex; height:5.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle m_=
{a}^{2}+m_{b}^{2}=3D5m_{c}^{2}=3D{\frac {5}{4}}c^{2}.}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>The median on the hypotenuse of a right triangle divides the triangle in=
to two isosceles triangles, because the median equals one-half the hypotenu=
se.
</p><p>The medians <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"=
><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"displ=
